give out 1) If you give out a number of things, you distribute them among a group of people. [V (not )] There were people at the entrance giving out leaflets. [Also V ] 2) If you give out information, you make it known to people. [V (not )] He wouldn't give out any information... [V ] How often do you give your phone number out? 3) If a piece of equipment or part of the body gives out, it stops working. [V ] All machines give out eventually... [V ] One of his lungs gave out entirely. 4) If you give out something such as a scream or a sigh, you sigh, scream, or make some other sound. [WRITTEN] [V (not )] He gave out a scream of pain. Syn: let out 5) see give off